# deploy/backup/crontab.example
#
# Example cron schedule for DocJob's Postgres + uploads backups. Install with
# (as the user that has `docker` group access on this host — see DEPLOY.md):
#   crontab -e
#
# Daily Postgres dump at 03:15, uploads archive at 03:30 (staggered so the two
# don't compete for disk I/O). Both scripts rotate their own output (default:
# keep the last 14 dumps/archives), so no separate cleanup entry is needed.
#
# Adjust /opt/docjob below to wherever you actually cloned the repo.

15 3 * * * /opt/docjob/deploy/backup/pg-backup.sh      >> /var/log/docjob-backup.log 2>&1
30 3 * * * /opt/docjob/deploy/backup/uploads-backup.sh >> /var/log/docjob-backup.log 2>&1
